title: 820-3476 orange light not turn on
message:
Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse at PM_PWRBTN_L (at same time).
If detected, check for pulse at PM_SLP_S4_L too.

title: 820-3476 orange light not turn on
message: Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and there is a pulse PM_PWRBTN_L,  but there is no pulse PM_SLP_S4.

title: 820-3476 orange light not turn on
message:
Then the problem is PCH related.
Check its basic signals; PM_BATLOW_L, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PCH_DSWVRMEN, SMC_ADAPTER_EN, PM_RSMRST_L and the 4 DC RTC signals.

title: 820-3476 orange light not turn on
message: PM_BATLOW_L=3.3v PM_DSW_PWRGD=3.4v PCH_DSWVRMEN=3.2 SMC_ADAPTER_EN=3.3v PM_RSMRST_L=3.3,   RTC_RESET_L=3.3v PCH_SRTCRST_L=3.3v  PCH_INTRUDER_L=3v PCH_INTVRMEN=3.1v

title: 820-3476 orange light not turn on
message:
Are you really sure no pulse at PM_SLP_S4_L, nor PM_SLP_S3_L?
In such case, PCH internal failure.
You can try to heat it (adding quality flux) and pray...
